# Dimension: Syllable

## Monosyllable Accuracy
- If the word has only ONE pronounced vowel sound, it must NOT be split.
- If monosyllabic but split = fail. If polysyllabic but unsplit = fail.

## Vowel Anchor Integrity
- Every segment must contain exactly ONE pronounced vowel sound.
- Exception: word-final syllabic "-le" counts as a vowel sound.

## Atomic Unit Preservation
- Consonant digraphs (sh, ch, th, ph, wh, ck, gh, gn, kn, ng, wr, sc, qu), vowel teams (ee, ea, ou, ai, ay, ey, ie, oa, oe, oo, ow, ue, ui), and R-controlled vowels (ar, er, ir, or, ur) must NEVER be split.
- ✗ "te·ach·er" (splits "ea") → ✓ "teach·er"

## Silent Letter Handling
- Silent letters must NOT form their own syllable. Attach to the preceding vowel's syllable.
- ✗ "ma·ke" → ✓ "make"

## Consonant Split Accuracy
- VCV: consonant attaches to the second vowel (pa·per).
- VCCV: split between consonants (sud·den). Double consonants must be split.

## Prefix Integrity
- Common prefixes (re-, un-, dis-, pre-, mis-) should stay visually intact where phonetics allow.
- ✓ "re·start" ✗ "res·tart"

## Separator Format
- Must use ONLY middle dot "·" (U+00B7). Any other separator = fail.

