# Dimension: Mnemonic — Roots & Affixes (词根词缀)

## Etymology Validity
- Root/affix breakdown must be scientifically accurate and documented in established etymological references.
- If the word is basic and indivisible, output must be `false`. Any forced breakdown = fail.
- REJECT fabricated or pseudo-etymology.

## Formula Accuracy
- Format: `component(中文含义) + component(中文含义) + ...`
- Every English component must have its correct Chinese meaning in parentheses.
- Suffix label must match the given POS (e.g., adj. → "形容词后缀").

## Chant–Formula Coherence
- Chant must logically summarize the formula. Must NOT introduce meanings not in the formula.

## Script 6-Step Framework
6 distinct paragraphs required: (1) 标准纠音, (2) 零件拆解, (3) 画面还原, (4) 逻辑合成, (5) 批量裂变, (6) 思维升华. Missing or merged = fail.

## Scene Logic
- Visual scene must be STRICTLY derived from the word's actual etymology and meaning.
- REJECT forced or random associations.

## Word Family Accuracy
- The 2–3 related words in Step 5 must genuinely share the exact same root. REJECT false cognates.

## Prop Ban
- No physical teaching props (flashcard, pointer, blackboard). Only "on screen" or mental imagination.

## Tone & Style
- Real-time live-stream style, colloquial, speak to "XX同学" with natural fillers. Reject rigid/AI tone.

