# Dimension: Mnemonic — Phonetic Association (音义联想)

## Phonetic Association Validity
- Chinese phonetic hook must have natural sound similarity ≥ 60% to the target word's pronunciation.
- Must be common and easily understood — not obscure or dialect-specific.
- REJECT semantically negative or inappropriate hooks (e.g., /bʌs/ ≈ "爸死").
- If no natural association exists, output must be `false`.

## Formula Accuracy
- Format: `/发音/ ≈ [中文谐音/象声词]`
- IPA transcription must be correct. Chinese hook must genuinely sound similar.

## Chant–Formula Coherence
- Chant must logically connect the phonetic hook to the target word's meaning.

## Script 6-Step Framework
6 distinct paragraphs required: (1) 标准纠音, (2) 谐音搜索, (3) 画面还原, (4) 逻辑合成, (5) 发音保护, (6) 思维升华. Missing or merged = fail.

## Scene Logic
- Visual scene must be directly built from the Chinese phonetic hook.
- Must bridge emotionally or logically to the target meaning.

## Pronunciation Firewall
- Step 5 must explicitly warn: the Chinese hook is ONLY a memory aid, NOT the pronunciation.
- Must return the student to the correct English sound.
- Must mention 1–2 words sharing a similar phonetic pattern.
- Omission = fail.

## Prop Ban
- No physical teaching props. Only "on screen" or mental imagination.

## Tone & Style
- Real-time live-stream style, colloquial, speak to "XX同学". Reject rigid/AI tone.

